This paper is primarily focused on game theory and convergence rates of fictitious play, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science - Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses tie-breaking methods, which could potentially fall under the category of cs.AI (Computer Science - Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses mathematical analysis to disprove a conjecture, which could fall under the category of cs.LG (Computer Science - Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Computer Science - Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses convergence rates, which could fall under the category of cs.IT (Computer Science - Information Theory).
